OL,6,FThe survey of 2,153 people carried out
OL,7,Fon August 20-21 found 37% of voters
OL,8,Fviewed immigration and asylum as the
OL,9,Fmost important issue facing the
OL,10,Fcountry, ahead of 25% who said the
OL,11,Feconomy and 7% who said the health
OL,12,Fservice.
OL,14,FLord Blunkett told the newspaper: "I
OL,15,Fthink that the individual measures the
OL,16,FGovernment has taken are extremely
OL,17,Fhelpful in their own right but don't
OL,18,Fadd up either to a comprehensive
OL,19,Fanswer or an understandable narrative.
